20553008@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The problem is that on the vital issue of monetary policy and exchange rates, conservative, free-market economists divide into at least three incompatible camps.@@@@1@24@@oe@2-2-2013
20553009@unknown@formal@none@1@S@There are the strict monetarists, who believe that floating exchange rates free an economy to stabilize its price level by stabilizing the monetary aggregates.@@@@1@24@@oe@2-2-2013
